Spring Boot Development Tools
- web application - plugin 'Live Reload'
- compile and restart Spring Boot upon changes:
  LIVE RELOAD
  - add maven dependency: GAV :: org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-devtools:xxx
    They will monitor the class files and compile class files to check for a change => trigger a reboot ..
    Do change, ReCompile >> app auto reboots

  - IntelliJ Ultimate : Run/Debug configurations >> SpringBoot >> MyRestMvcApplication >>
        >> Add Run Option >> SpringBoot
            >> On 'update' action  >  Do nothing / [ Update classes and resources ] / ..
            >> On  frame deactivation > [ Update classes and resources ]
        Upon source code changes, it does not need to press Recompile; it will not restart immediately, but once the active window is changed forth/back (to avoid restart with every Save action)..


